Hi Celina, Thanks for meeting with me earlier! During our call, we confirmed that the Transaction Sync (bulk/historical) to Zamp is still not functioning, despite clearing the Zamp-related Scheduled Actions and verifying that an order did not have a Zamp Transaction Sync Status of "Successful". Here's my Calendly link to schedule a call for next week or after if preferred: https://calendly.com/chris-zamp/30min These are the options for clearing any Zamp Tax-related transaction sync records and effectively "resetting" these items: Utilizing the WP-CLI Command via WP-CLI access. This involves creating a file, similar to the attached wp-cli-zamp-reset.php , within the store's theme or a must-use plugin. Run it with the command wp zamp reset-sync . Run the below functions via functions.php - see the attached file. Run the below SQL queries in phpMyAdmin or a similar tool. 2) The functions to run: function reset_zamp_sync_data() {
if (!current_user_can('manage_woocommerce')) {
return 'Insufficient permissions';
}

// Clean up scheduled actions
if (class_exists('ActionScheduler')) {
as_unschedule_all_actions('zamp_process_transactions_batch', array(), 'zamp-transactions-sync');
}

// Clean up options
global $wpdb;
$wpdb->query("DELETE FROM {$wpdb->options} WHERE option_name LIKE 'zamp_sync_%'");
$wpdb->query("DELETE FROM {$wpdb->options} WHERE option_name LIKE 'zamp_transactions_queue_%'");

// Reset sync status
update_option('zamp_sync_status', 'ready');

// Clear transaction status meta
$wpdb->query("DELETE FROM {$wpdb->postmeta} WHERE meta_key IN ('zamp_transaction_status', 'zamp_transaction_date', 'zamp_transaction_error')");

return 'Zamp sync data has been completely reset';
}

// Uncomment to run (then comment back after running once)
// add_action('init', function() {
// if (current_user_can('manage_woocommerce') && isset($_GET['reset_zamp_sync'])) {
// echo reset_zamp_sync_data();
// exit;
// }
// }); 3) The SQL queries: -- Clear scheduled actions
DELETE FROM wp_options WHERE option_name LIKE 'zamp_sync_%';
DELETE FROM wp_options WHERE option_name LIKE 'zamp_transactions_queue_%';

-- Reset sync status
INSERT INTO wp_options (option_name, option_value, autoload) 
VALUES ('zamp_sync_status', 'ready', 'yes') 
ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE option_value = 'ready';

-- Clear transaction status meta
DELETE FROM wp_postmeta 
WHERE meta_key IN ('zamp_transaction_status', 'zamp_transaction_date', 'zamp_transaction_error'); Overall, we're hoping to accomplish the following items somehow: Clean up scheduled actions via Zamp_Transaction_Sync_Batch::cleanup_scheduled_actions() Clear any scheduled events with wp_clear_scheduled_hook('zamp_process_transactions_event') Zamp_Transaction_Sync_Batch::cleanup_scheduled_actions() - Removes all scheduled batch processing tasks Zamp_Transaction_Sync_Batch::cleanup_sync_data() - Removes all sync progress and queue data from the options table

Account: https://admin.zamp.com/companies/cm8nj1w0100e903l58e6834dz Transactions: https://admin.zamp.com/companies/cm8nj1w0100e903l58e6834dz/transactions?date=2024-01-01~2025-06-06 There are two issues: Transactions in Zamp show no tax collected, but they collected tax via Stripe Tax. Calculations from Zamp aren't returning tax collected, even with Stripe Tax disabled. Notes from the call: Before Zamp, they were using Stripe Tax's plugin for WooCommerce. Taxes calculate fine with Stripe Tax, but they're listed as a different tax line from what Zamp would look for (state + jurisdiction name combination). They're also using WooCommerce Subscriptions. Zamp-specific steps: They had the correct API token for Zamp, but we replaced it and saved anyway. Nexus states are correctly configured in Zamp and Woo. Tax calcs and transaction sync were enabled. Debug mode was enabled today (6/6/25). Disabled Stripe Tax and placed an order with only Zamp Tax enabled, no tax was calculated. Re-enabled Stripe Tax, and the tax was calculated. They have the default PTC enabled. Addresses appear to be formatted fine. No transactions in Zamp are showing tax collected, although tax was collected. Example is TR-1348 shown in the screenshot below. Order ID TR-1348: The transaction sync from 6/3/25: Reviewing the logs: The 6/3/25 log file shows a bunch of 409/conflict errors, meaning the transaction already exists. There are a few subtotal, shipping, and tax errors, where issues with amounts may occur (but only in 5 out of 100+ orders). The 6/5/25 log file shows a bunch of attempts to start tax calculations, but the addresses only contain "state":"AZ" The log files from today ( 6/6/25 ) appear to show successful tax calcs, but no taxes were shown on orders in Zamp, or test checkout orders (not entirely placed): Address for my test: 1395 S Arizona Ave, Chandler, AZ 85286 There's a 400 bad_request error at 2025-06-06T13:07:39+00:00 due to: Receiving lineItems and quantity as string values instead of numbers (I think?) The 2nd 6/6/25 log file shows more of the error noted below (received string instead of number). This error is repeated for calculations a few times: 2025-06-06T13:07:38+00:00 ERROR [ZAMP_TAX] [ERROR] API returned non-200 status: 400
2025-06-06T13:07:39+00:00 ERROR [ZAMP_TAX] [ERROR] API response received: {
    "code": "BAD_REQUEST",
    "message": "Input validation failed",
    "issues": [
        {
            "code": "invalid_type",
            "expected": "number",
            "received": "string",
            "path": [
                "lineItems",
                0,
                "quantity"
            ],
            "message": "Expected number, received string"
        }
    ]
}

Confirmed in testing that this address doesn't return a validated address response and I'll need to dig into the logs further, to see if I can find anything. The request: {
